article.headline: Kennesaw St. 74, Campbell 64
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. (AP) -- Ronell Wooten became the ninth Kennesaw State player to reach the 1,000-point plateau with his 21-point performance that led the Owls to a 74-64 victory over Campbell on Friday night, snapping a three-game losing streak. Jon-Michael Nickerson added a career-high 19 points and Golden Ingle had 10 assists for the Owls (9-15, 5-7 Atlantic Sun Conference). The Camels (10-12, 5-7) lost their second game in a row. Freshman standout Jonathan Rodriguez scored 19 points for Campbell, which had four players score in double figures. Eric Smith scored 13 points while Kyle Vejraska added 12 and Reggie Bishop 11.
